The theory of relativity is a scientific explanation of how time and space are connected. It was first proposed by Albert Einstein in the early 20th century. The theory of relativity comes in two parts: general relativity and special relativity.

Special relativity is the simpler of the two theories. It explains that the laws of physics are the same for everyone, no matter how fast they are moving or in which direction.
